I've created the `ArgoRolloutsAddOn` class in `lib/addons/argorollouts/argoRollouts.ts`. This addon follows the same pattern as the ArgoCD addon but is specifically for installing Argo Rollouts.

The implementation:

1. Uses the official Argo Helm chart repository
2. Installs Argo Rollouts in a dedicated namespace (default: "argo-rollouts")
3. Allows customization of the installation through values
4. Includes a cleanup mechanism that properly uninstalls Argo Rollouts when the stack is deleted

To use this addon in your project, add it to your list of addons:

```typescript
import { ArgoRolloutsAddOn } from "./lib/addons/argorollouts/argoRollouts";

const addons = [
  // Other addons...
  new ArgoRolloutsAddOn({
    namespace: "argo-rollouts", // optional, default is "argo-rollouts"
    version: "2.32.0",          // optional, default is "2.32.0"
    createNamespace: true,      // optional, default is true
    cleanupEnabled: true,       // optional, default is true
    values: {
      // Optional custom values for the Helm chart
      dashboard: {
        enabled: true
      }
    }
  })
];

EksBlueprint.builder()
  .account(account)
  .region(region)
  .addOns(...addons)
  .build(scope, stackID);
```

The addon is now ready to use in your EKS Blueprints project.

